time required: 45 minutes
---

Pre-heat your #oven to 220 degrees. Peel and finely chop up your @garlic{1%clove} and roughly chop your @chestnut mushrooms{1}. Peel and cut your @carrots{2} into sticks. We chopped the @diced chorizo{⅔%pack} for you to save a bit of time!

Pat the @British chicken thighs{8} skin dry with some #kitchen towel. Rub a ¼ tsp of @olive oil{1/4%tsp} on each thigh and rub in a good pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook them in the #oven on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} until the skin is nice and crispy. Rest them out of the oven afterwards.

> We added the baking step to get that classic roasted chicken texture.

Heat @olive oil{1%tsp} in a pan on medium heat. Once it's hot add in the chorizo. When the chorizo has browned off slightly add in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> Tip: Be careful not to burn the garlic

Add in the @chopped tomatoes{1%can}, mushrooms and @bay leaf{1}. Next stir in @?sugar{1%tsp} (if you have it) and a good pinch of salt and pepper. Leave to bubble away on low heat until it has thickened up (about ~{15%minutes}).

Bring a large #pot of salted water to the boil and add in your @new potatoes{700%g}. After ~{12%minutes} add the @carrots{2} to the #pot and cook everything together for another ~{4%minutes}.

> Tip: Cooking the carrots with the potatoes saves on dirty pans and boiling more water

The potatoes should be soft enough to slip a sharp knife through them by now. Drain the water and put the carrots in a separate #bowl. Let the potatoes dry off and crush them lightly with a #fork. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat up a #non-stick pan{} with @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} on high heat and add the @rosemary{1} leaves. Cook for ~{1%minute} then add the potatoes and cook until they are nicely crisped up (about ~{5%minutes}).

> Tip: You can re-heat the carrots with the potatoes for the last minute

Serve your carrots and crushed new potatoes in a bowl with the chicken thighs. Pour your chorizo infused tomato sauce over the top. In your most dramatic matador's voice shout "Olé!" as you serve it on the table.